[{"id":32139,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"States of Matter","question":"","options":["$\\frac{2}{3}$","$\\frac{1}{3} \\times \\frac{273}{298}$","$\\frac{1}{3}$","$\\frac{1}{2}$"],"answer":2,"solution":"Let the mass of methane and oxygen is $w$\n$\\begin{aligned}\n& \\text { mole fraction of oxygen }=\\frac{\\frac{w}{32}}{\\frac{w}{32}+\\frac{w}{16}} \\\\\n& =\\frac{\\frac{1}{32}}{\\frac{1}{32}+\\frac{1}{16}}=\\frac{\\frac{1}{32}}{\\frac{3}{32}}=\\frac{1}{3}\n\\end{aligned}$\nLet the total pressure be $\\mathrm{P}$\nThe pressure exerted by oxygen (partial pressure) $=\\mathrm{X}_{\\mathrm{O}_2} \\times \\mathrm{P}_{\\text {total }}$\n$\\Rightarrow \\mathrm{P} \\times \\frac{1}{3}$\nHence, (C) is correct.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2007","image":null},{"id":32124,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"States of Matter","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>28</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>14</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>7</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>09</mn></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"As per Graham&#39;s law,<br /><br /><math> <mrow> <mfrac> <mrow> <msub> <mtext>V</mtext> <msub> <mtext>SO</mtext> <mn>2</mn> </msub> </msub> <mo>/</mo> <msub> <mtext>t</mtext> <msub> <mtext>SO</mtext> <mn>2</mn> </msub> </msub> </mrow> <mrow> <msub> <mtext>V</mtext> <msub> <mtext>O</mtext> <mn>2</mn> </msub> </msub> <mo>/</mo> <msub> <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi> <msub> <mtext>O</mtext> <mn>2</mn> </msub> </msub> </mrow> </mfrac> <mo>=</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <msub> <mtext>p</mtext> <msub> <mtext>SO</mtext> <mn>2</mn> </msub> </msub> </mrow> <mrow> <msub> <mtext>p</mtext> <msub> <mtext>O</mtext> <mn>2</mn> </msub> </msub> </mrow> </mfrac> <msqrt> <mfrac> <mrow> <msub> <mtext>M</mtext> <msub> <mtext>O</mtext> <mn>2</mn> </msub> </msub> </mro