ssure, gas particles are difficult to compress.","Gas particles have negligible volume."],"answer":2,"solution":"At high pressures gas particles are difficult to compress rather they are not compressible at all.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2015 (10 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":32132,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"States of Matter","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">*</mi></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mo>:</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mo>:</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mn>1</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mo>:</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.128</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mo>:</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.225</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">*</mi></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mo>:</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mo>:</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mn>1</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mo>:</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.225</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mo>:</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.128</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">*</mi></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mo>:</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mo>:</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mn>1</mn><mo>.225</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mo>:</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.128</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mo>:</mo><mn>1</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">*</mi></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mo>:</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mo>:</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mn>1</mn><mo>.128</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mo>:</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.225</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mo>:</mo><mn>1</mn></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>*</mo></msup><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>RT</mi></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi></mfrac></msqrt><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;1</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">.</mi><mn>414</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">:</mi><mn>1</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">.</mi><mn>595</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">:</mi><mn>1</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">.</mi><mn>732</mn></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover accent=\"true\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mn>8</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#960;</mi></mfrac><mfrac><mi>RT</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi></mfrac></msqrt></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>RT</mi></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi></mfrac></msqrt></math><br /><br /><math><mrow><msqrt><mn>2</mn> </msqrt> <mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mo>:</mo><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><msqrt> <mrow> <mfrac> <mn>8</mn> <mrow> <mn>3.14</mn> </mrow> </mfrac> </mrow> </msqrt> <mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mo>:</mo><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><msqrt> <mn>3</mn> </msqrt> </mrow> </math><br /><br /><math> <mrow> <mn>1</mn><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mo>:</mo><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mn>1.128</mn><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mo>:</mo><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mn>1.225</mn> </mrow> </math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>*</mo></msup><mo>:</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>&#175;</mo></mover><mo>:</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>:&#160;</mo><mn>1</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">.</mi><mn>128</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>:&#160;</mo><mn>1</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">.</mi><mn>225</mn></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2013 (07 Apr)","image":null},{"id":32150,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"States of Matter","question":"","options":["only Boyle’s law","only Charles’ law","only Avogadro’s law","all of these"],"answer":3,"solution":"No Solution Available","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2002","image":null},{"id":32127,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"States of Matter","question":"","options":["temperature is sufficiently high and pressure is low.","both temperature and pressure are very low.","both temperature and pressure are very high.","temperature is sufficiently low and pressure is high."],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>At very high temperatures &amp; low pressures, the characteristic constant&nbsp;behaviour can be understood from virial&nbsp;expansion<br /><br /><math> <mrow> <mtext>Z</mtext> <mo>=</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <msub> <mtext>PV</mtext> <mtext>m</mtext> </msub> </mrow> <mrow> <mtext>RT</mtext> </mrow> </mfrac> <mo>=</mo> <mn>1</mn> <mo>+</mo> <mfenced close=\")\" open=\"(\" separators=\",\"> <mrow> <mtext>b</mtext> <mo>-</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <mtext>a</mtext> </mrow> <mrow> <mtext>RT</mtext> </mrow> </mfrac> </mrow> </mfenced> <mfrac> <mrow> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> <mrow> <msub> <mtext>V</mtext> <mtext>m</mtext> </msub> </mrow> </mfrac> <mo>+</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <msup> <mtext>b</mtext> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> <mrow> <msubsup> <mtext>V</mtext> <mtext>m</mtext> <mn>2</mn> </msubsup> </mrow> </mfrac> <mo>+</mo> <mtext>....</mtext> </mrow> </math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></msub></math>, molar volume large i.e&nbsp;<math> <mrow> <mfrac> <mrow> <msup> <mtext>b</mtext> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> <mrow> <msubsup> <mtext>V</mtext> <mtext>m</mtext> <mn>2</mn> </msubsup> </mrow> </mfrac> <mo>&#8594;</mo> <mtext>o</mtext> </mrow> </math><br /><br />i.e Third term in virial expansion can be ignored.</p><p>In qualitative terms, the real gas will show ideal behaviour when the intermolecular forces of attraction will be negligible which is possible at high temperature and low pressure.<br />Also&nbsp;<math> <mrow> <mfenced close=\")\" open=\"(\" separators=\",\"> <mrow> <mtext>b</mtext> <mo>-</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <mtext>a</mtext> </mrow> <mrow> <mtext>RT</mtext> </mrow> </mfrac> </mrow> </mfenced> <mo>&#8594;</mo> <mtext>o</mtext> </mrow> </math><br /><br />i.e.&nbsp;<math> <mrow> <mtext>Z</mtext> <mo>&#8776;</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> </math>&nbsp;and gas behaves ideally.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2014 (09 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":32123,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"States of Matter","question":"","options":["Hydrogen bond","Ion-ion interaction","Ion-dipole interaction","London force"],"answer":0,"solution":"For Hydrogen bond which is a case of dipole-dipole interaction, intermolecular force<br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>F</mtext><mo>&#8733;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">r</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mfrac></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">r</mi></math> is distance between two dipoles","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2015 (04 Apr)","image":null},{"id":32085,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"States of Matter","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/4f4c998d-6e12-4300-9e2d-c04e6bb3349a-image.png\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 170px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/26ac6263-081b-4633-9861-efd5349de1b4-image.png\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 158px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/a1c62f9e-94ba-43e3-a6b3-3239c4caa1d9-image.png\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 157px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ad2bd5cd-484a-4bb6-81c0-2c613ba1ea17-image.png\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 158px;\" />"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>PV</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>nRT</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">w</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mfrac><mi>RT</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>dRT</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi></mfrac></math> so <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>&#8733;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi></math> Slope&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>RT</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi></mfrac></math></p><p>Greater is slope greater is Temperature.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/6ed24572-e6f8-4b99-8827-2433e0a84d64-image.png\" style=\"width: 160px; height: 152px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (27 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":32093,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"States of Matter","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></mrow><mn>1</mn></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></msub></mfrac><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>300</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>3</mn></msup></mrow><mn>300</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>6</mn></msup></mrow><msub><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></msub></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>1200</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>927</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (25 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":32104,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"States of Matter","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Mol of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>NaClO</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math> <math><mo>=</mo></math>&nbsp;Mol&nbsp;of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></p><p>Mol of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>PV</mi><mi>RT</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>492</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.082</mo><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>300</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mi>mol</mi></math><br />&nbsp;</p><p>Mass of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>NaClO</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>106</mn><mo>.5</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>2130</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (08 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":32142,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"States of Matter","question":"","options":["$\\left(\\frac{x}{x+1}\\right) P$","$\\left(\\frac{2 x}{1-x}\\right) P$","$\\left(\\frac{x}{x-1}\\right) P$","$\\left(\\frac{x}{1-x}\\right) P$"],"answer":0,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/vXMkC0VmX2b0N_of4OXjhkdXRloFdQY007246AiK_m0.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2006","image":null},{"id":32071,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"States of Matter","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>From&nbsp;Boyle&#39;s Law,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>940</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn></math>&nbsp;mm of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Hg</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo></math>&nbsp;Pressure at which volume is reduced by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>40</mn><mo>%</mo></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo></math>&nbsp;Volume decreased by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>40</mn><mo>%</mo></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#160;</mo><mfenced><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p>Then,<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>940</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>1567</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>16</mn><mo>&#160;</mo></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8776;</mo><mn>1567</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>Hg</mi></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (10 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":32116,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"States of Matter","question":"","options":["at low pressure, real gases show ideal behaviour.","at very low temperature, real gases show ideal behaviour.","at Boyle&#39;s temperature, real gases show ideal behaviour.","at very large volume, real gases show ideal behaviour."],"answer":1,"solution":"A real gas behaves like ideal gas at high temperature and low pressure. At very low temperature intermolecular forces of attraction will be quite significant as molecular randomness is very low due to which at very low temperature real gases can&#39;t show ideal behaviour.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2017 (08 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":32096,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"States of Matter","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Total moles of gases,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>4</mn></msub></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><msub><mi>CO</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></msub></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow><mn>16</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow><mn>44</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn></math></p><p>Now,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>nRT</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>314</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>300</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>10</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>49652</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>5</mn></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>Pa</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>149</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>652</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kPa</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8776;</mo><mn>150</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kPa</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (17 Mar Shift 1)","image":null}]